experience: Some previous work-related skill, knowledge, or experience is usually needed. For example, a teller would benefit from experience working directly with the public.
education: These occupations usually require a high school diploma.
job_training: Employees in these occupations need anywhere from a few months to one year of working with experienced employees. A recognized apprenticeship program may be associated with these occupations.
example: These occupations often involve using your knowledge and skills to help others. Examples include orderlies, counter and rental clerks, customer service representatives, security guards, upholsterers, tellers, and dental laboratory technicians.
svp_desc: Individuals workers typically need anywhere from minimum of 3 and 6 months- up to 2 years- to learn the techniques, acquire the information, and develop the facility needed for average performance in specific situations.

work_tasks.title: Cutting and Slicing Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
work_tasks.task: Set up, operate, or tend machines that cut or slice materials, such as glass, stone, cork, rubber, tobacco, food, paper, or insulating material.
work_tasks.descr: Set up, operate, or tend machines that cut or slice materials, such as glass, stone, cork, rubber, tobacco, food, paper, or insulating material.

work_tasks.title: Cutting and Slicing Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
work_tasks.task: Review work orders, blueprints, specifications, or job samples to determine components, settings, and adjustments for cutting and slicing machines.
work_tasks.descr: Review work orders, blueprints, specifications, or job samples to determine components, settings, and adjustments for cutting and slicing machines.

work_tasks.title: Cutting and Slicing Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
work_tasks.task: Examine, measure, and weigh materials or products to verify conformance to specifications, using measuring devices, such as rulers, micrometers, or scales.
work_tasks.descr: Examine, measure, and weigh materials or products to verify conformance to specifications, using measuring devices, such as rulers, micrometers, or scales.

work_tasks.title: Cutting and Slicing Machine Setters, Operators, and Tenders
work_tasks.task: Wash stones, using water hoses.
work_tasks.descr: Wash stones, using water hoses.

work_tasks.task: Remove completed materials or products from cutting or slicing machines, and stack or store them for additional processing.

work_tasks.task: Press buttons, pull levers, or depress pedals to start and operate cutting and slicing machines.
work_tasks.descr: Press buttons, pull levers, or depress pedals to start and operate cutting and slicing machines.

work_tasks.task: Start machines to verify setups, and make any necessary adjustments.
work_tasks.descr: Start machines to verify setups, and make any necessary adjustments.

work_tasks.task: Feed stock into cutting machines, onto conveyors, or under cutting blades, by threading, guiding, pushing, or turning handwheels.

work_tasks.task: Clean and lubricate cutting machines, conveyors, blades, saws, or knives, using steam hoses, scrapers, brushes, or oil cans.
work_tasks.descr: Clean and lubricate cutting machines, conveyors, blades, saws, or knives, using steam hoses, scrapers, brushes, or oil cans.

work_tasks.task: Monitor operation of cutting or slicing machines to detect malfunctions or to determine whether supplies need replenishment.
